<p id="Par22" class="p">Fitting a power function (Eq. 
 <xref rid="Equ1" ref-type="" class="xref">1</xref>) between fluvial sediment load (
 <italic class="italic">Q</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">d</italic>
 </sub>) and water discharge (
 <italic class="italic">Q</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">s</italic>
 </sub>) is a commonly used method to develop sediment rating curves for rivers
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR60" class="xref">60</xref>–
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR64" class="xref">64</xref>
 </sup>. From the empirical relationship between 
 <italic class="italic">Q</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">s</italic>
 </sub> (km
 <sup class="sup">3</sup> yr
 <sup class="sup">−1</sup>) and 
 <italic class="italic">Q</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">d</italic>
 </sub> (Mt/yr) the following correlation can be established:
 <disp-formula id="Equ1" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">1</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M1" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${Q}_{d}=a.{{Q}_{s}}^{b}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M2" display="block" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">Q</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">d</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mi class="mi">a</mi>
    <mo class="mo">.</mo>
    <msup class="msup">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">Q</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">s</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mi class="mi">b</mi>
    </msup>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="41598_2019_45442_Article_Equ1.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>where, 
 <italic class="italic">a</italic> is the sediment rating coefficient and 
 <italic class="italic">b</italic> is the rating exponent.
</p>
